 "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "zss.simple_tree.Node", "bases": ["object"], "methods": [{"name": "zss.simple_tree.Node.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "label", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "children", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "zss.simple_tree.Node.get_children", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "node", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Default value of `get_children` argument of {py:func}`zss.distance`.\n\n```\nreturns\n\nself.children.\n```\n"]}, {"name": "zss.simple_tree.Node.get_label", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "node", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Default value of `get_label` argument of {py:func}`zss.distance`.\n\n```\nreturns\n\nself.label.\n```\n"]}, {"name": "zss.simple_tree.Node.addkid", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "node", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "before", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Add the given node as a child of this node."]}, {"name": "zss.simple_tree.Node.get", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "label", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": [":returns: Child with the given label."]}, {"name": "zss.simple_tree.Node.iter", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Iterate over this node and its children in a preorder traversal."]}, {"name": "zss.simple_tree.Node.__contains__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "b", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "zss.simple_tree.Node.__eq__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "b", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "zss.simple_tree.Node.__ne__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "b", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "zss.simple_tree.Node.__repr__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "zss.simple_tree.Node.__str__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["A simple node object that can be used to construct trees to be used with\n{py:func}`zss.distance`.\n\nExample:\n\n```\nNode(\"f\")\n    .addkid(Node(\"a\")\n        .addkid(Node(\"h\"))\n        .addkid(Node(\"c\")\n            .addkid(Node(\"l\"))))\n    .addkid(Node(\"e\"))\n```\n"]}], "exports": []}, {"name": "zss.compare", "documentation": ["!/usr/bin/env python", "-*- coding: utf-8 -*-", "Authors: Tim Henderson and Steve Johnson", "Email: tim.tadh@gmail.com, steve@steveasleep.com", "For licensing see the LICENSE file in the top level directory."], "functions": [{"name": "zss.compare.py_zeros", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "dim", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "pytype", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "zss.compare.strdist", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "a", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "b", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "zss.compare.simple_distance", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "A", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "B", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "get_children", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "get_label", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "label_dist", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "return_operations", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Computes the exact tree edit distance between trees A and B.\n\nUse this function if both of these things are true:\n\n- The cost to insert a node is equivalent to `label_dist('', new_label)`\n- The cost to remove a node is equivalent to `label_dist(new_label, '')`\n\nOtherwise, use {py:func}`zss.distance` instead.\n\n```\nparam A\n\nThe root of a tree.\n\nparam B\n\nThe root of a tree.\n\nparam get_children\n\nA function get_children(node) == [node children].  Defaults to\n.\n\nparam get_label\n\nA function get_label(node) == 'node label'.All labels are assumed\nto be strings at this time. Defaults to .\n\nparam label_dist\n\nA function\nlabel_distance((get_label(node1), get_label(node2)) >= 0.\nThis function should take the output of get_label(node) and return\nan integer greater or equal to 0 representing how many edits to\ntransform the label of node1 into the label of node2. By\ndefault, this is string edit distance (if available). 0 indicates that\nthe labels are the same. A number N represent it takes N changes to\ntransform one label into the other.\n\nparam return_operations\n\nif True, return a tuple (cost, operations)\nwhere operations is a list of the operations to transform A into B.\n\nreturn\n\nAn integer distance [0, inf+)\n```\n"]}, {"name": "zss.compare.distance", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "A", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "B", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "get_children", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "insert_cost", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "remove_cost", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "update_cost", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "return_operations", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Computes the exact tree edit distance between trees A and B with a\nricher API than {py:func}`zss.simple_distance`.\n\nUse this function if either of these things are true:\n\n- The cost to insert a node is **not** equivalent to the cost of changing\n  an empty node to have the new node's label\n- The cost to remove a node is **not** equivalent to the cost of changing\n  it to a node with an empty label\n\nOtherwise, use {py:func}`zss.simple_distance`.\n\n```\nparam A\n\nThe root of a tree.\n\nparam B\n\nThe root of a tree.\n\nparam get_children\n\nA function get_children(node) == [node children].  Defaults to\n.\n\nparam insert_cost\n\nA function insert_cost(node) == cost to insert node >= 0.\n\nparam remove_cost\n\nA function remove_cost(node) == cost to remove node >= 0.\n\nparam update_cost\n\nA function update_cost(a, b) == cost to change a into b >= 0.\n\nparam return_operations\n\nif True, return a tuple (cost, operations)\nwhere operations is a list of the operations to transform A into B.\n\nreturn\n\nAn integer distance [0, inf+)\n```\n"]}], "variables": [{"name": "zss.compare.zeros", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "zss.compare.zeros", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "zss.compare.REMOVE", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "zss.compare.INSERT", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "zss.compare.UPDATE", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "zss.compare.MATCH", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "zss.compare.AnnotatedTree", "bases": ["object"], "methods": [{"name": "zss.compare.AnnotatedTree.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "root", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "get_children", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "zss.compare.Operation", "bases": ["object"], "methods": [{"name": "zss.compare.Operation.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "op", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "arg1", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "arg2", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "zss.compare.Operation.__repr__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "zss.compare.Operation.__eq__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "other", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [{"name": "zss.compare.Operation.remove", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "zss.compare.Operation.insert", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "zss.compare.Operation.update", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "zss.compare.Operation.match", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Dummy class for storing edit operations"]}], "exports": []}]}